{"TopicId":196680,"ForumId":15,"TopicTitle":"What do you use to DXT5 compress .dds files?","CreatedByName":"Pipcard","CreatedById":2541,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-03T03:32:45Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Pipcard","CreatedById":2541,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-03T03:32:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m trying to save a grayscale heightmap and I tried the .dds export plugin for GIMP but it leaves RGB color artifacts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd I can\u0027t save uncompressed because only DXT5 compression works with KSP 1.8 and up.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-09-03T05:09:06Z\u0022 title=\u002209/03/2020 05:09  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 3, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Pipcard\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"R-T-B","CreatedById":200868,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-03T04:29:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre you using windows or linux?\u00A0 If windows, you may try paint.net.\u00A0 If Linux, well, you already tried GIMP...\u00A0 so dunno.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pipcard","CreatedById":2541,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-03T04:56:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223848271\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196680\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221599107364\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022200868\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022R-T-B\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n27 minutes ago, R-T-B said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre you using windows or linux?\u00A0 If windows, you may try paint.net.\u00A0 If Linux, well, you already tried GIMP...\u00A0 so dunno.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI tried paint.net and am getting the same result as GIMP: slightly purple artifacts when it should all be shades of gray.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(by the way, I\u0027m trying to edit the Earth heightmap from Real Solar System)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Scq7X24.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002249.47\u0022 height=\u0022466\u0022 width=\u0022942\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/Scq7X24.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-09-03T04:57:28Z\u0022 title=\u002209/03/2020 04:57  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 3, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Pipcard\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pipcard","CreatedById":2541,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-03T05:56:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI asked \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/203367-katniss218/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022203367\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/203367-katniss218/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Katniss218\u003C/a\u003E on Discord and they said they use \u003Ca href=\u0022https://vvvv.org/contribution/texconvgui\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ETexConvGUI\u003C/a\u003E (unzip with 7zip), with the output format being R16_UNORM for 16-bit grayscale heightmaps and BC3_UNORM for colored textures (or they just use GIMP for the latter).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI first saved to a .png then used the converter.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-09-03T06:19:00Z\u0022 title=\u002209/03/2020 06:19  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 3, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Pipcard\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"R-T-B","CreatedById":200868,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-03T06:10:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223848275\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196680\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221599109016\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00222541\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Pipcard\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Pipcard said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI tried paint.net and am getting the same result as GIMP: slightly purple artifacts when it should all be shades of gray.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(by the way, I\u0027m trying to edit the Earth heightmap from Real Solar System)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Scq7X24.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002249.47\u0022 height=\u0022466\u0022 width=\u0022942\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/Scq7X24.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI see.\u00A0 I honestly have no idea, was just a stab in the dark.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}